The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Johnsville had a population of 22. Of the residents, 18 were [[White Americans|White]], 1 was [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 was from [[Race (United States Census)|some other race]], and 2 were from two or more races. There were 2 [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] residents (from any race).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Johnsville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0637512 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 22, 2025}}</ref>

There were 10 households, of which 6 were [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] and 2 were one person living alone.<ref>{{cite web |title=Johnsville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0637512 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 22, 2025}}</ref> The median age was 60.5{{nbsp}}years.

There were 72 housing units, of which 10 were occupied year round, all by homeowners, and 61 were used seasonally.<ref name=DP1/>

